         <abstract>
            <p>  A Church service made up of psalms, biblical readings and hymns. Four types of Saʿātāt have been identified by <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Taft1986Liturgy"/>
                  <citedRange unit="page">266</citedRange>
               </bibl>:</p>
            <p> 
               <title ref="LIT2230Saatat"/>: the Coptic Saʿātāt;</p>
            <p> 
               <title ref="LIT3575Mashaf"/>: the Saʿātāt of <persName ref="PRS4709Giyorgis">Giyorgis of Saglā</persName>, 
               which replaced the <title ref="LIT2230Saatat"/>:  and is presently in use in Ethiopia and Eritrea;</p>
            <p>
               <title ref="LIT3576Saatat"/>:  a Saʿātāt that includes the entire Psalter in the daily pensum;</p>
            <p>
               <title ref="LIT3577GizeS"/>: a cursus of prayers which is not really a Saʿātāt, but a Gize ṣalot for hermits and recluses.</p>
         </abstract>
